@startuml Bounded Contexts Relationship
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam rectangle {
    BackgroundColor #E1F5FE
    BorderColor #01579B
    BorderThickness 2
}

title IoT Pilot Bounded Contexts

' Core Bounded Contexts
rectangle "Device Management Context" as DeviceContext {
    rectangle "Device" as Device
    rectangle "SSH Session" as SshSession
    rectangle "Device Command" as DeviceCommand
}

rectangle "User Management Context" as UserContext {
    rectangle "User" as User
    rectangle "Session" as Session
    rectangle "Authentication" as Auth
}

rectangle "Customer Management Context" as CustomerContext {
    rectangle "Customer" as Customer
    rectangle "Subscription" as Subscription
    rectangle "Billing" as Billing
}

rectangle "Monitoring Context" as MonitoringContext {
    rectangle "Metric" as Metric
    rectangle "Alert" as Alert
    rectangle "Threshold" as Threshold
}

' Shared Kernel
rectangle "Shared Kernel" as SharedKernel {
    rectangle "Tenant Context" as TenantContext
    rectangle "Domain Events" as DomainEvents
    rectangle "Value Objects" as ValueObjects
}

' Supporting Contexts
rectangle "Analytics Context" as AnalyticsContext {
    rectangle "Reports" as Reports
    rectangle "Dashboards" as Dashboards
    rectangle "Data Export" as DataExport
}

rectangle "Notification Context" as NotificationContext {
    rectangle "Email Service" as Email
    rectangle "SMS Service" as SMS
    rectangle "Webhook Service" as Webhook
}

' Infrastructure Services
rectangle "Infrastructure Services" as Infra {
    rectangle "Message Queue" as Queue
    rectangle "Cache Service" as Cache
    rectangle "File Storage" as Storage
}

' Context Relationships
DeviceContext --> UserContext : User executes\ncommands on devices
DeviceContext --> CustomerContext : Devices belong\nto customers
DeviceContext --> MonitoringContext : Device metrics\nand alerts
DeviceContext --> SharedKernel : Uses shared\nvalue objects

UserContext --> CustomerContext : Users belong\nto customers
UserContext --> SharedKernel : Uses tenant\ncontext

CustomerContext --> SharedKernel : Uses tenant\ncontext

MonitoringContext --> DeviceContext : Monitors\ndevice health
MonitoringContext --> CustomerContext : Customer-specific\nthresholds
MonitoringContext --> NotificationContext : Sends alerts
MonitoringContext --> SharedKernel : Uses shared\nevents

AnalyticsContext --> MonitoringContext : Analyzes\nmetrics data
AnalyticsContext --> DeviceContext : Device\nusage analytics
AnalyticsContext --> CustomerContext : Customer\nusage reports

NotificationContext --> UserContext : Notifies\nusers of events
NotificationContext --> CustomerContext : Customer-specific\nnotifications

' Anti-Corruption Layer
SharedKernel --> Infra : Infrastructure\nabstraction

' Upstream Dependencies
Infra --> DeviceContext : Device connectivity
Infra --> MonitoringContext : Metrics collection
Infra --> UserContext : Session storage
Infra --> NotificationContext : Message delivery

' Context Map Legend
legend right
    |= Context |= Responsibility |
    | Device | Device lifecycle & connectivity |
    | User | Authentication & authorization |
    | Customer | Multi-tenant management |
    | Monitoring | Metrics & alerting |
    | Analytics | Reporting & insights |
    | Notification | Alert delivery |
    | Shared Kernel | Cross-cutting concerns |
    | Infrastructure | External services |
endlegend

' Context Boundaries
note right of DeviceContext : Device Management\n- Device registration\n- SSH connections\n- Command execution\n- Device lifecycle
note right of UserContext : User Management\n- Authentication\n- Authorization\n- Session management\n- User profiles
note right of CustomerContext : Customer Management\n- Multi-tenancy\n- Subscriptions\n- Resource quotas\n- Billing
note right of MonitoringContext : Monitoring & Alerting\n- Metrics collection\n- Threshold evaluation\n- Alert management\n- Health monitoring
note right of SharedKernel : Shared Kernel\n- Tenant isolation\n- Domain events\n- Common value objects\n- Base classes
note right of AnalyticsContext : Analytics & Reporting\n- Data aggregation\n- Report generation\n- Dashboard creation\n- Data export

@enduml
